item.title: Josh Caterer discusses Smoking Popes "Megan"
item.description: In 1997, Smoking Popes released their major label debut album Destination Failure. Buried deep in the record's track listing was "Megan", a heartfelt song that resonated with fans and became one of the band's signature songs. In this episode, vocalist and guitarist Josh Caterer discusses the song's origins and its somewhat mysterious narrative. Feed: https://feeds.megaphone.fm/JJW5546407535

item.title: You Don’t Fail, Diets Do | Ep.52
item.description: Diets are, by nature, set up to fail. Yet, we are made to believe that we are the failures when we gain the weight back. In this episode, Chanci shares a response she wrote to a vulnerable email sent in by a brave woman who is ready for freedom. May it serve you too. Learn more about the It Tastes Like Freedom group program HERE Let’s connect! Leave me a voice message here. Leave Chanci an email here. Feed: https://feeds.captivate.fm/it-tastes-like-freedom/
